Make the Web malloc implementation a SCons build option (default dlmalloc, upstream-identical)

Godot 4.4.1 does not set -sMALLOC for the web build, so Emscripten's default (dlmalloc) is
used. dlmalloc serialises EVERY allocation through a SINGLE GLOBAL LOCK. That is the measured
root cause of VOXIVERSE's streaming hitch (docs/COSMOS-WALK-PERF-DESIGN.md): our voxel workers
perform ~500-2000 heap ops per generated block, so N workers + the main thread convoy on that
one lock. Because a browser main thread may not block in Atomics.wait, a contended lock
BUSY-WAITS on the main thread, burning the rAF budget.

Measured live on a real GPU (2026-07-17), which is what makes this a diagnosis and not a guess:
  * all 6 pool threads read ACTIVE on GenerateBlock for an entire drain, yet only ~40 blocks/s
    come out -- the pool runs at full width and every thread CRAWLS;
  * phys_ms inflates 4.3 -> 44.5 ms for IDENTICAL physics/movement code purely because workers
    are busy (the main thread's own unrelated code slows ~10x);
  * drain-rate vs worst_ms correlates r = -0.47 (bidirectional coupling = a shared serializer,
    not a one-way bottleneck);
  * movement itself is FREE (moving with gen<=5 => worst p50 23.4 == standing 23.2);
  * godot_voxel's own main-thread work is nil (VoxelTerrain _process breakdown 0.02-0.08 ms,
    apply queue empty) -- so the cost is not meshing, applying, draws, or movement.
This one mechanism also explains why raising the voxel worker count (FP-M1b, 2 -> 6/10) bought
nothing: more workers simply add contenders to the convoy.

mimalloc uses per-thread heaps and removes the convoy. Emscripten has shipped it since 3.1.50
(-sMALLOC=mimalloc); VOXIVERSE pins EMSDK_VERSION=3.1.64, so it is available. Emscripten's own
benchmarks show dlmalloc ANTI-SCALING with threads while mimalloc restores scaling.

Rather than hard-code the flag (which rots silently against upstream and cannot be A/B'd), it is
exposed as a SCons option `malloc` defaulting to "dlmalloc" -- byte-identical to stock when unset,
so this patch is INERT unless build-engine.sh passes malloc=mimalloc from versions.env WEB_MALLOC.
Revert knob: set WEB_MALLOC=dlmalloc and rebuild (~24 min).

NEVER-OOM note: mimalloc reserves per-thread segments, so the baseline WASM heap is expected to
grow. This is a memory-costly upgrade and MUST be shipped as a measured deploy-time A/B (peak heap
via the COSMOS-FP-M2-HEAP-AB harness), and REJECTED if the baseline grows past the ledgered
ceiling. Memory safety outranks frame time -- that rule is not negotiable for a frame-time win.

